sentences: Peter Dijkstra (born 11 June 1978) is a Dutch conductor, especially of choirs and vocal ensembles.
Born in Roden, Drenthe, Dijkstra sang in his youth in Jongenskoor Roder, a boys' choir, which his father, Bouwe Dijkstra, founded in 1985.
Dijkstra has been guest conductor of the Netherlands Chamber Choir and artistic director of the Chor des Bayerischen Rundfunks of Munich from September 2005.
In 2007 he was appointed chief conductor of the Swedish Radio Choir.
Grammy Award with Chor des Bayerischen Rundfunks (2008)
